32:09.127 --> 32:13.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Twenty-year-old Naadiya Cellars
was placed
in foster care five years ago
after her mother

32:13.498 --> 32:18.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
died. She's now encouraging
Pittsburgh residents
to consider becoming foster
parents. Naadiya

32:18.904 --> 32:22.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
says it's often difficult to get
people to
simply remember that they are
kids.

32:22.107 --> 32:23.842 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NAADIYA CELLARS, Former Foster
Youth: The
hardest part about being in
foster care is

32:23.875 --> 32:28.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that you are not allowed to do
everything
else that everybody else is
allowed to do.

32:28.613 --> 32:32.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Like, all the rules, like, you
are not allowed
to spend the night at your
friend's house

32:32.050 --> 32:34.719 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
unless they have clearances.
Those are always
the hardest parts.

32:34.753 --> 32:40.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID SANDERS: They want to be
seen as young
people who are facing life's
challenges, have

32:40.559 --> 32:45.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the same dreams that any other
young person
has, but so often the fact that
they have

32:45.130 --> 32:50.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been in foster care, they feel
like they are
then stigmatized as being
failures or unlikely

32:50.602 --> 32:52.103 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to succeed.

32:52.137 --> 32:55.407 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think one of the most
important things
