so if they
are trying to pull me back, I
will suicide

38:24.636 --> 38:26.571 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
here.

38:26.604 --> 38:30.308 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: At the camp
that's been sheltering
the Pakistanis next to the
detention center,

38:30.341 --> 38:34.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
volunteer Ayesha Keller had this
advice for
would-be travelers waiting on
the Turkish

38:34.913 --> 38:36.648 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
coast.

38:36.681 --> 38:39.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AYESHA KELLER, Volunteer: At the
moment, I
don't think it's worth risking
your life to

38:39.150 --> 38:44.055 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
cross over to Lesbos or one of
the other Greek
islands, because it's so unclear
what the

38:44.088 --> 38:50.195 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
situation is. It just doesn't
make sense on
a humanitarian level. And I
thought the E.U.

38:50.228 --> 38:54.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was about protecting human
rights, and now
they have agreed to something
like this.

38:54.566 --> 38:59.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I understand what they're trying
to do. I
understand that they want to cut
down smuggling

38:59.070 --> 39:04.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and they want to cut down people
crossing
in a dangerous way. But this
doesn't just

39:04.075 --> 39:08.313 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
seem to be a sensible solution.
And it's just
going to increase smuggling, as
